    {
        title: "04. Common Cyber Attacks",
        content: "<ul><li><strong>Phishing:</strong> Deceptive emails to steal data.</li><li><strong>Malware:</strong> Malicious software (Viruses/Ransomware).</li><li><strong>Password Attacks:</strong> Brute-forcing or stealing credentials.</li><li><strong>Social Engineering:</strong> Manipulating people into giving up info.</li></ul>"
    },
    {
        title: "05. How Access is Gained",
        content: "<ul><li>Weak or reused passwords across accounts.</li><li>Clicking malicious links in 'urgent' emails.</li><li>Using outdated software with known vulnerabilities.</li><li>Connecting to unsecured public Wi-Fi.</li></ul>"
    },
    {
        title: "06. Real-World Examples",
        content: "<ul><li><strong>Corporate Breaches:</strong> Massive data leaks involving millions of users.</li><li><strong>Social Media Hijacks:</strong> Losing control of personal identities.</li><li><strong>Financial Scams:</strong> Direct theft via online banking fraud.</li></ul>"
    },
    {
        title: "07. Effects of Hacking",
        content: "<ul><li>Financial loss for individuals and companies.</li><li>Severe privacy invasion.</li><li>Identity theft leading to long-term legal issues.</li><li>Emotional stress and loss of digital trust.</li></ul>"
